data.enText: to change the form of sth

data.chText: 光化学反应使光变为电脉冲。
data.enText: The photochemical reactions transform the light into electrical impulses.

data.chText: 使改变外观（或性质）；使改观
data.enText: to completely change the appearance or character of sth, especially so that it is better

data.chText: 新的色彩调配将使你的卧室焕然一新。
data.enText: A new colour scheme will transform your bedroom.

data.chText: 那是能够彻底改变我一生的一件事。
data.enText: It was an event that would transform my life.

simple_means.memory_skill: trans 变换 + form 形状，形式 → 变形；改造

ex.chText: 女巫把那男孩变成了一只老鼠。
ex.enText: A witch changed the boy into a mouse.

ex.chText: 经济形势已发生了相当大的变化。
ex.enText: The economic situation has changed considerably.
The leaves on the trees change colour in the autumn.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，可指任何变化，强调与原先的情况有明显的不同。

ex.chText: 你的外衣太大了，得找人改一下。
ex.enText: Your coat is too big. You must have it altered.

ex.chText: 工作环境必须改善，以适应新的要求。
ex.enText: The working condition must be altered to meet the new requirements.

synonyms.bx: 常指轻微改变，强调在保持原状的情况下进行局部改变。

ex.chText: 请把这钱兑换成人民币。
ex.enText: Please convert this money into RMB.
Her mother has converted to Catholicism.

synonyms.bx: 指改变形式、用途、使用方式等，也指改变信仰、观点、态度等。

ex.chText: 这项计划要用就必须修改。
ex.enText: The plan must be modified if it is to be used.

ex.chText: 你最好说得和缓些才是。

synonyms.bx: 指对某物作细小的改动以对其进行改进，使其更适用或更高效。

ex.chText: 魔术师把那条手帕变成了一只鸟。
ex.enText: The magician transformed the handkerchief into a bird.

ex.chText: 太阳能可以转化为能量。
ex.enText: Solar energy can be transformed into power.

synonyms.bx: 指在形式、外观、性质等方面彻底改变，即成为全新的东西。

ex.enText: Coal can be turned into heat.

ex.chText: 他把这本小说变成了英语畅销书。
ex.enText: He turned this novel into an English best-seller.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指外形、颜色、气味、性质等方面发生变化。

ex.chText: 鱼的价格随着市场行情而变化。
ex.enText: The prices of fish vary according to market conditions.

ex.chText: 老年人不喜欢改变他们的习惯。
ex.enText: Old people don't like to vary their habits.

synonyms.bx: 指根据某一情况的变化而变化，也指更改某事物。

tr: change in outward structure or looks
example: The salesman metamorphosed into an ugly beetle

tr: increase or decrease (an alternating current or voltage)
change (a bacterial cell) into a genetically distinct cell by the introduction of DNA from another cell of the same or closely related species
convert (one form of energy) to another
change or alter in form, appearance, or nature
example: She transformed the clay into a beautiful sculpture

tr: change from one form or medium into another

value.def: To transform something into something else means to change or convert it into that thing.

example.ex: Your metabolic rate is the speed at which your body transforms food into energy...
example.tran: 新陈代谢率是身体把食物转换为能量的速度。

example.ex: Delegates also discussed transforming them from a guerrilla force into a regular army.
example.tran: 代表们还讨论了把他们从游击队武装改造为正规军的问题。

example.ex: Norah made plans for the transformation of an attic room into a study...
example.tran: 诺拉计划把一个阁楼间改建成书房。

value.def: To transform something or someone means to change them completely and suddenly so that they are much better or more attractive.

example.ex: The Minister said the Urban Development Corporation was now transforming the area...
example.tran: 部长声称城市开发公司如今正使该地区改头换面。

example.ex: A cheap table can be transformed by an interesting cover…
example.tran: 一块趣味盎然的桌布就能使一张廉价桌子面目一新。

example.ex: He said she had transformed him from a hard-drinking womaniser into a devoted husband and father.
example.tran: 他说她已经把他由一个酗酒玩女人的浪荡子彻底改造成了一位忠诚的丈夫、一位慈爱的父亲。

value.tran: 改善;使改观;使改头换面

example.ex: In the last five years he's undergone a personal transformation.
example.tran: 过去 5 年里他整个人发生了全新的转变。

example.ex: …one of the most astonishing economic transformations seen since the second world war.
example.tran: 二战以来最惊人的经济改革之一
